Furthermore, the GP method requires the application of a regression formula obtained via the ARG method to calculate an absolute value. Similarly, the Gjedde–Patlak–Matsuda method also involves a regression formula determined by the Kanno–Lassen method [19]. The simple non-invasive \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
